## Validation steps (detailed)

0) Preconditions

Job accepted with job_id, spec, seed, duration_steps, checkpoints_every, min_validators=3.

Worker posts claim: {job_id, merkle_root, artifact_uri, signature, timestamp}.


1) Select witness nodes

Coordinator chooses 3 candidate validators satisfying:

Distinct IP/ASN/region, >X km apart (configurable).

Different device types / sensor modalities if possible.

Sufficient stake & positive reputation.


Coordinator publishes the list of selected validators and challenge_window (e.g., 60s).

2) Challenge derivation (each validator)

Using challenge_seed = H(job_id || merkle_root || block_hash), each validator independently derives:

k indices: indices = PRF(challenge_seed || validator_id) mod total_checkpoints (choose e.g., 3 indices each).

an optional light-replay spec: replay_steps = PRF(... ) % max_replay_steps (e.g., 50 steps).

a telemetry sample window: t0, t1 to request telemetry from worker for cross-check.


3) Request proofs from worker

Validators contact worker (or fetch artifact_uri) and request:

Merkle path proofs for selected indices (worker returns checkpoint_blob, merkle_proof).

A small selected log snippet / telemetry timeseries (signed by worker) for time interval [t0,t1] including telemetry + geo + sensor hashes.

Optional: request an on-demand challenge: run replay_steps from checkpoint Ci and return H(replay_output || Ci_index || validator_id).


4) Local verification

Each validator performs:

Verify the worker’s signature on Merkle root/claim.

Validate Merkle path → root.

Validate checkpoint deterministic fingerprint (optionally re-run a light deterministic verification or check deterministic hash).

Verify telemetry consistency: compare worker telemetry vs validator’s own telemetry expectations (see cross-correlation below).

Validate geo/time: worker telemetry contains signed GNSS fix, timestamp; check plausibility (worker close enough to where job was expected to run).

Validate replay hash if requested by re-executing N steps or running a reduced-fidelity validator (fast).


If all pass → validator emits a signed attestation: accept. If any check fails → reject with structured reasons and evidence.

5) Attestation collection

Coordinator waits challenge_window for attestations:

If ≥3 accept from distinct validators → claim accepted.

If any reject → dispute resolution: escalate to additional validators (e.g., neutral auditors) or perform full replay. If >= threshold of reject or conflicting votes → reject job, slash worker stake.



